## 11. Agent Teams

Form teams for cross-cutting changes; single-agent for narrow edits.

| Team | Agent ID | Owned Paths | Domain | Model | Effort |
|------|----------|-------------|--------|-------|--------|
| tech-lead | `tech-lead` | All | orchestration, planning | opus | max |
| {{TEAM_1_NAME}} | `{{TEAM_1_ID}}` | `{{TEAM_1_PATHS}}` | {{TEAM_1_DOMAIN}} | {{TEAM_1_MODEL}} | {{TEAM_1_EFFORT}} |
| {{TEAM_2_NAME}} | `{{TEAM_2_ID}}` | `{{TEAM_2_PATHS}}` | {{TEAM_2_DOMAIN}} | {{TEAM_2_MODEL}} | {{TEAM_2_EFFORT}} |
| security | `security-team` | All | review secrets, auth, encryption | opus | max |

Spawn a team when:
- Change spans >3 files across distinct domains.
- Security-sensitive code is touched (auth, crypto, secrets, network boundaries).
- Major version bump (breaking changes).

Otherwise the main agent works solo with `explorer` / `code-reviewer` as needed.
